    "Description": "Valerio Belli is the first great engraver of rock crystal and other semiprecious stones of the Renaissance.  The subject of this plaque is Christian, indeed, the shape suggests a freestanding devotional work, but the firm, athletic, precisely modeled bodies reflect Belli's admiration of the aesthetics of classical, pagan antiquity.\r\n\r\nThe artist has signed his name in Latin on the Roman-style pedestal base of a broken column behind St. Joseph.  With great virtuosity, Belli has defined the perspective of the simple roof with a vanishing point behind the column, creating a deep space behind the frieze-like arrangement of the figures.\r\n",
